<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Echoes — User Guide</title>
<style>
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    background: #0f0e0d;
    color: #e8e0d5;
    font-family: Georgia, serif;
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding: 40px 24px 80px;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  header {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 60px 0 48px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }
  .logo {
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: normal;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  section {
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #A0714F;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  h3 {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: normal;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }
  p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .step-num {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid #A0714F;
    color: #A0714F;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .step-content h4 {
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: normal;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .step-content p {
    font-size: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .capsule-box {
    border: 1px solid rgba(160, 113, 79, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 28px;
    background: rgba(160, 113, 79, 0.05);
    margin: 24px 0;
  }
  .capsule-box h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: #A0714F;
  }
  .divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    margin: 48px 0;
  }
  .mood-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 16px;
  }
  .mood-item {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
  }
  .mood-item .emoji { font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .mood-item .name { font-size: 14px; color: #fff; }
  .mood-item .desc { font-size: 12px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35); font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; }
  footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 48px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="logo">Echoes</div>
  <h1>User Guide</h1>
  <div class="subtitle">leave a mark in the places you've been</div>
</header>

<section>
  <h2>What is Echoes</h2>
  <p>Echoes lets you record short voice memories and anchor them to the exact GPS coordinates where you are. When you return to that place, the app quietly reminds you that a memory is waiting.</p>
  <p>No account. No cloud. No tracking. Everything stays on your device.</p>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Recording an Echo</h2>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Open the app</h4>
      <p>You'll see your map with all your existing Echoes as colored pins. Your current location is shown in the center.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Tap the record button</h4>
      <p>Press the microphone button at the bottom of the map. The app will start listening.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Speak your moment</h4>
      <p>You have 8 seconds. Say what you feel, where you are, what you notice. Keep it honest and unfiltered.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Stop and review</h4>
      <p>Tap Stop when you're done. You can listen back and retry if needed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Save your Echo</h4>
      <p>Tap Continue. Echoes will analyze your voice and suggest a mood and tags automatically. Give it a title, adjust the mood if you like, then tap "Leave this Echo here."</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Mood Detection</h2>
  <p>Echoes analyzes your voice transcription on-device using AI to suggest a mood. You can always change it manually.</p>

  <div class="mood-grid">
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">☀️</div>
      <div class="name">Happy</div>
      <div class="desc">Joyful, excited, grateful</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">🌧️</div>
      <div class="name">Melancholic</div>
      <div class="desc">Sad, lonely, heartbroken</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">🌫️</div>
      <div class="name">Nostalgic</div>
      <div class="desc">Memories, past, childhood</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">🕯️</div>
      <div class="name">Intimate</div>
      <div class="desc">Home, warmth, closeness</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">🌊</div>
      <div class="name">Restless</div>
      <div class="desc">Anxious, nervous, uneasy</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">🌙</div>
      <div class="name">Suspended</div>
      <div class="desc">Uncertain, waiting, thinking</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mood-item">
      <div class="emoji">🍃</div>
      <div class="name">Light</div>
      <div class="desc">Calm, free, peaceful</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Time Capsule</h2>

  <div class="capsule-box">
    <h3>🔒 Lock an Echo until a future date</h3>
    <p>When saving an Echo, you can set an unlock date. The Echo will appear on your map as a locked pin — you won't be able to listen to it until that day arrives.</p>
    <p>When you physically return to that place after the unlock date, the app notifies you that your capsule is ready to be opened.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Record as usual</h4>
      <p>Record your 8-second voice memo and tap Continue.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Enable Time Capsule</h4>
      <p>In the edit screen, toggle on "Time Capsule" and choose a future date — one week, one month, one year, or any custom date.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Leave it there</h4>
      <p>Save your Echo. It will appear on the map with a lock icon. You won't be able to open it until the date arrives.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Return and listen</h4>
      <p>On or after the unlock date, walk back to that place. Echoes will notify you that the capsule is open. Tap it and hear your past self.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Proximity Notifications</h2>
  <p>When you walk near a place where you left an Echo, the app sends you a quiet notification: <em>"There is an Echo nearby."</em></p>
  <p>Echoes monitors the 20 closest Echoes to your current location. No battery drain — iOS handles this natively in the background.</p>
  <p>To receive notifications, make sure you have granted notification permissions in Settings → Echoes.</p>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Sharing an Echo</h2>
  <p>Open any Echo and tap "Share this Echo." Echoes generates a beautiful image with your title, transcription, mood, waveform, date and GPS coordinates.</p>
  <p>Share it to Instagram, WhatsApp, or save it to your camera roll.</p>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Archive</h2>
  <p>Tap the archive icon to see all your Echoes in a list. You can search by title or transcription, and filter by mood.</p>
  <p>Tapping an Echo in the archive centers the map on that location.</p>
</section>

<hr class="divider">

<section>
  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>Echoes does not collect any data. Your voice memos never leave your device unless you explicitly share them. There is no account, no login, no analytics.</p>
  <p>If you have iCloud enabled, your Echoes are backed up to your private iCloud storage — accessible only to you.</p>
</section>

<footer>
  ECHOES · VOICE MEMORIES · 2026
</footer>

</body>
</html>
